<TITLE> Sports commentator Khoda Bakhsh dies </TITLE>
<TEXT>
 Rajshahi, Mar 30 (bdnews24.com)  Sports commentator Khoda Bakhsh Mridha died in Rajshahi on Tuesday morning. He was 68. Mridha died at around 8:30 am, his son-in-law Sirajul Alam Bachchu told bdnews24.com. He said that his father-in-law had been suffering from pneumonia for the last few days. His condition deteriorated on Tuesday morning and he died on his way to Rajshahi Medical College Hospital. Rajshahi mayor Khariruzzaman Liton, former mayor Mizanur Rahman Minu and other well known people visited his house and gave condolences to the bereaved family. Mridha had served as a sports commentator in Bangladesh Television and Bangladesh Radio and participated in many programmes at home and abroad. bd
